import itertools

n = int(input())

ans = 0

for x in itertools.combinations_with_replacement(range(1, 4), n):
    if sum(x) != 6:
        ans += 1

print(ans % 1000000007)

    n = int(input().strip())
    res = 0

        res += math.factorial(n) // (math.factorial(i) * math.factorial(n - i))
